@page "/about"
@page "/info"
@* Two @page directives on one component -> its `routes` property is a two-element list
   ["/about", "/info"]. Routable pages are reached at runtime by the Router (via routes), which is
   why there is no RENDERS edge INTO a page — only page -> child-component RENDERS edges exist.
   This page is intentionally a thin stub: the full tour (stats, legend, and every demonstration)
   now lives on the Home page. Keeping the component here preserves the sample's only multi-route
   page — the pinned `routes = ["/about", "/info"]` fact — without duplicating that content. *@

<h1>About EdgeHop</h1>

<p class="lead">
    EdgeHop builds a queryable graph of a .NET + JavaScript solution and serves it to Claude Code over
    an MCP server, so it can answer structural questions without grepping. This very app is the sample
    it indexes. (This page is itself served by one component with two routes — <code>/about</code> and
    <code>/info</code> — so its node carries both templates.)
</p>

